{"timestamp":1774455644448,"source_app":"agentic-harness","session_id":"8cf9b770-0a7c-4949-a04c-8551e6126b00","hook_event_type":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01EC4SseejBFX6MLVT3zNoNU","payload":{"session_id":"8cf9b770-0a7c-4949-a04c-8551e6126b00","transcript_path":"/Users/auto/.claude/projects/-Users-auto-agentic-harness-apps-mas-trees-16abcd2e/8cf9b770-0a7c-4949-a04c-8551e6126b00.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/16abcd2e","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/16abcd2e/specs/issue-16abcd2e-adw-a94bcfc7-sdlc_planner-savings-amount-display-discount.md","content":"# Plan: Add savings amount display alongside discount percentage in discount template\n\n## Task Description\n\nAdd a `display-savings` attribute to the discount template component. When present, the component renders the absolute savings amount (e.g. \"Save $120/yr\") alongside the existing discount percentage. When absent, behavior is unchanged (percentage only).\n\nThe savings amount is computed as `priceWithoutDiscount - price`, formatted using the existing locale-aware `formatRegularPrice` utility, and given a period suffix (`/yr` or `/mo`) derived from the `recurrenceTerm` returned by that utility.\n\n## Relevant Files\n\n| File | Action | Why |\n|------|--------|-----|\n| `web-components/src/discount/template.js` | **Edit** | Core logic \u2014 add savings computation and conditional rendering |\n| `web-components/src/discount/index.js` | Read-only | Verify `discount` export still works after signature change |\n| `web-components/src/price/utilities.js` | Read-only | Understand `formatRegularPrice` inputs/outputs for currency formatting |\n| `web-components/src/price.js` | Read-only | Verify context shape passed to discount template (`{ ...settings, ...options }`) |\n| `web-components/test/discount/template.test.js` | **Edit** | Add test cases for `display-savings` on/off |\n\n## Step by Step Tasks\n\n### 1. Update `createDiscountTemplate` to accept and use context\n\nIn `web-components/src/discount/template.js`:\n\n- Import `formatRegularPrice` from `'../price/utilities.js'`\n- The inner render function already receives `(context, value)`. `context` contains all options from the element (including `displaySavings`, `formatString`, `commitment`, `term`, `usePrecision`, `locale`, `country`). `value` contains `price`, `priceWithoutDiscount`.\n- Add logic: if `context.displaySavings` is truthy AND both prices are valid, compute savings and render it.\n\n```js\nimport { isPositiveFiniteNumber } from '@dexter/tacocat-core';\nimport { formatRegularPrice } from '../price/utilities.js';\n\nconst getDiscount = (price, priceWithoutDiscount) => {\n    if (\n        !isPositiveFiniteNumber(price) ||\n        !isPositiveFiniteNumber(priceWithoutDiscount)\n    )\n        return;\n    return Math.floor(\n        ((priceWithoutDiscount - price) / priceWithoutDiscount) * 100,\n    );\n};\n\n// Map recurrenceTerm values to period suffix strings\nconst periodSuffix = { MONTH: '/mo', YEAR: '/yr' };\n\nconst createDiscountTemplate = () => (context, value) => {\n    const { price, priceWithoutDiscount } = value;\n    const discount = getDiscount(price, priceWithoutDiscount);\n\n    // Base percentage span \u2014 unchanged behavior\n    const percentageSpan =\n        discount === undefined\n            ? `<span class=\"no-discount\"></span>`\n            : `<span class=\"discount\">${discount}%</span>`;\n\n    // Savings amount span \u2014 only when display-savings attribute is present\n    if (context.displaySavings && discount !== undefined) {\n        const savingsAmount = priceWithoutDiscount - price;\n        const formatted = formatRegularPrice({\n            ...value,\n            price: savingsAmount,\n        });\n        const suffix = periodSuffix[formatted.recurrenceTerm] ?? '';\n        const savingsSpan = `<span class=\"discount-savings\">${formatted.accessiblePrice}${suffix}</span>`;\n        return `${percentageSpan}${savingsSpan}`;\n    }\n\n    return percentageSpan;\n};\n\nexport { getDiscount, createDiscountTemplate };\n```\n\n### 2. Verify `index.js` export is unaffected\n\n`web-components/src/discount/index.js` calls `createDiscountTemplate()` with no arguments. The outer factory still takes no arguments \u2014 no change needed.\n\n### 3. Add/update unit tests\n\nIn `web-components/test/discount/template.test.js`, add:\n\n- Test: `display-savings` absent \u2192 renders only `<span class=\"discount\">10%</span>` (existing behavior, no regression)\n- Test: `display-savings` present with valid prices \u2192 renders percentage span AND savings span with formatted amount + period suffix\n- Test: `display-savings` present but prices invalid \u2192 renders `<span class=\"no-discount\"></span>` only (no savings span)\n- Test: `display-savings` present with YEAR commitment \u2192 savings span ends with `/yr`\n- Test: `display-savings` present with MONTH commitment \u2192 savings span ends with `/mo`\n\nThe test fixtures need a minimal context with `formatString`, `commitment`, `term`, `usePrecision` to exercise `formatRegularPrice`.\n\n### 4. Validate syntax\n\nRun `node --check` on modified files to confirm no syntax errors.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- When `display-savings` attribute is absent, the rendered HTML is identical to current behavior (only `<span class=\"discount\">N%</span>` or `<span class=\"no-discount\"></span>`).\n- When `display-savings` is present and prices are valid, a second `<span class=\"discount-savings\">` element is appended with the locale-formatted savings amount and `/yr` or `/mo` suffix.\n- When `display-savings` is present but prices are missing/invalid, only `<span class=\"no-discount\"></span>` is rendered (no savings span).\n- Currency symbol and separators reflect the locale from `formatString` \u2014 no hardcoded `$` or USD assumption.\n- All existing tests pass without modification.\n\n## Validation Commands\n\n```bash\nnode --check web-components/src/discount/template.js\nnode --check web-components/test/discount/template.test.js\n```\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EC4SseejBFX6MLVT3zNoNU"}}
